98 and no enemies - human interest story
 All Human Being should live so long as to be this kind of old! I AGREE!
=20
 Toward the end of Sunday service, the Minister asked, "How many of you have
forgiven your enemies?"
=20
 80% held up their hands.
=20
 The Minister then repeated his question. All responded this time, except o=
ne
small elderly lady.
=20
 "Mrs. Neely, are you not willing to forgive your enemies?"
=20
 "I don't have any," she replied, smiling sweetly.
=20
 "Mrs. Neely, that is very unusual. How old are you?"'
=20
 "Ninety-eight," she replied.=20
=20
 The congregation stood up and clapped their hands.
=20
 "Mrs. Neely, would you please come down in front & tell us all how a person
can live ninety-eight years & not have an enemy in the world?"
=20
 The little sweetheart of a lady tottered down the aisle, faced the
congregation, and said, "I outlived the bitches."
=20
